# MUI Design System

Read [docs/DESIGN.md](../../docs/DESIGN.md) before adding or changing UI.

## Stack

- MUI only — `@mui/material`, theme in `src/theme/`
- Primitives in `src/components/ui/`

## NEVER

- Hard-coded colors (`#`, `rgb()`, `rgba()`)
- Inline `fontWeight` on Typography — use theme variants
- Custom Button/Card when a ui primitive exists
- Tailwind or utility-class layout

## ALWAYS

- Check `src/components/ui/` before creating new UI
- Use typography variants: `marketing*` for landing, `app*` for dashboard
- Use palette keys: `primary.main`, `text.secondary`, `background.dark`, etc.
- One `h1` per page

## Imports

| Need | Import |
|------|--------|
| Marketing section | `@/components/ui/MarketingSection` |
| Marketing heading | `@/components/ui/MarketingSectionHeader` |
| App page title | `@/components/ui/PageHeader` |
| App section | `@/components/ui/PageSection` |
| Card surface | `@/components/ui/AppCard` |
| Empty state | `@/components/ui/EmptyStatePanel` |
| Form layout | `@/components/ui/FormColumn` |
| Dark CTA | `@/components/ui/InvertedButton` |
| Stars | `@/components/ui/StarRating` |

## sx rule

If an `sx` block exceeds ~15 lines, extract to a primitive or theme token.
